---
import MarketingChrome from "../layouts/MarketingChrome.astro";

const title = "Privacy Policy · Bolt TMS";
const lastUpdated = "May 2026";
---

<MarketingChrome title={title} description="How Bolt handles information on this marketing site and related services.">
    <div class="marketing-shell">
    <article class="max-w-3xl text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-white/70">
        <h1 class="scroll-mt-24 text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-white">Privacy policy</h1>
        <p class="text-[14px] text-white/50">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
        <p class="mt-5">
            This policy describes how Bolt System (“Bolt,” “we”) handles personal
            information collected through this marketing website, the Bolt TMS application
            at app.bolttms.com, and related sales or support interactions. Replace this
            draft with counsel-approved language before relying on it in customer
            agreements.
        </p>
        <h2 class="mt-10 scroll-mt-24 text-xl font-semibold text-white">What we collect</h2>
        <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-5">
            <li>Contact details you provide (name, email, company, phone) when you sign up, schedule a demo, or email us.</li>
            <li>Usage and device data typical of web and SaaS products (logs, approximate location from IP, cookies where used).</li>
            <li>Operational data you enter into Bolt TMS for transportation management.</li>
        </ul>
        <h2 class="mt-10 scroll-mt-24 text-xl font-semibold text-white">How we use information</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
            We use information to deliver and improve Bolt TMS, respond to requests,
            secure our services, analyze product usage in aggregate, and communicate about
            your account or transactions. Marketing communications require an opt-in
            where required by law.
        </p>
        <h2 class="mt-10 scroll-mt-24 text-xl font-semibold text-white">Sharing</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
            We share information with subprocessors that help us host, secure, or operate
            the service (for example cloud hosting or email delivery), under contracts that
            limit use to providing services to us. We may disclose information to comply
            with law or protect rights and safety.
        </p>
        <h2 class="mt-10 scroll-mt-24 text-xl font-semibold text-white">Retention &amp; security</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
            We retain data as needed to provide the service, meet legal obligations, and
            resolve disputes. We apply reasonable technical and organizational safeguards,
            acknowledging that no method of transmission or storage is perfectly secure.
        </p>
        <h2 class="mt-10 scroll-mt-24 text-xl font-semibold text-white">Your choices</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
            Depending on jurisdiction, you may have rights to access, correct, delete, or
            export personal data, or to object to certain processing. Contact us at
            <a href="mailto:support@boltsystem.com">support@boltsystem.com</a>
            to exercise those rights.
        </p>
        <h2 class="mt-10 scroll-mt-24 text-xl font-semibold text-white">Contact</h2>
        <p class="mt-3">
            Bolt System · Nashville, TN ·
            <a href="mailto:support@boltsystem.com">support@boltsystem.com</a>
        </p>
    </article>
    </div>
</MarketingChrome>
